text: The Davaoeño people, (Davaoeño: mga "Davaoeño") are the visayan and mindanaoan ethnic cultural group in the southernmost Philippines, The Davaoeño people are native local in Davao Region particularly in Metro Davao, Manobo, Mansaka, Chavacano, Cebuano and southern Tagalog are the Davaoeño speakers.http://www.ethnicgroupsphilippines.com/ethnic-groups-in-the- philippines/davaoeno The Cebuano people is natively Cebuano speakers of Davaoeños than the Tagalog people and other Mindanao hilitribal group. They are also understand to each other to communicate in Visayan community, in some parts of Northern Mindanao, Zamboanga Peninsula and Caraga.http://relatedwords.org/davaoe%C3%B1o%20people ==References== Category:Ethnic groups in the Philippines
title: Davaoeño people
